dr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 For \uc2 Business in the Community\uc2  (BITC), the UK charity that runs the awards announced at the Royal Albert Hall in London on Tuesday night, winners must show tangible social and environmental impact. Two companies receive the Responsible Business of the Year Award: the regional utility \uc2 Anglian Water Services\uc2  and \u8212\'20\'14 in the small and medium enterprises category \u8212\'20\'14 We Are Vista, a creative communications agency.\par \par \uc2 The judges were impressed by Anglian\u8217\'20\'19s wide-ranging Love Every Drop strategy, which promises to \u8220\'20\'1Cfundamentally change\u8221\'20\'1D how the company works. Goals include cutting pollution, waste and water leakages. Starting in 2010, Anglian cut its operational carbon footprint by 10 per cent by 2015 and carbon emissions from capital construction projects by half. It aims for net carbon neutrality by mid-century. The company built solar arrays and wind turbines and favours suppliers that support its goals.\par \par \uc2 We Are Vista takes a similarly broad approach. The agency promotes diversity, personal development and employee volunteering while also reducing its environmental impact. A five-year sustainability plan includes a 20 per cent cut in office energy consumption and a 30 per cent decrease in waste to landfill by 2019.\par \par \uc2 While both companies have set ambitious sustainability targets, their leaders stress that meeting these requires businesses to go beyond statements from executives or handing over the work to a \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  (CSR) department. Anglian made a conscious decision not to create such a unit, says Peter Simpson, chief executive. \u8220\'20\'1CWe don\u8217\'20\'19t have a separate strategy associated with being a responsible business \u8212\'20\'14 that is the strategy. There is only one.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 James Wilkins, managing director of We Are Vista, also warns of the dangers of treating sustainability as an add-on. \u8220\'20\'1CIf you\u8217\'20\'19re not careful, it becomes a series of measures that you manage and audit rather than something you\u8217\'20\'19re mobilising people [to tackle],\u8221\'20\'1D he says.\par \par \uc2 Companies must clearly articulate sustainability goals and create targets that are ambitious but tangible and related to their business, he adds.\par \par \uc2 Businesses\u8217\'20\'19 definitions of sustainability vary and this is reflected in the diversity of award winners. \uc2 National Grid\uc2 , a winner of the BITC Award for Environmental Leadership, focused on greenhouse gases from energy generation. The company included a requirement for carbon reduction in its tendering process.\par \par \uc2 Tesco\uc2  \u8212\'20\'14 winner of the Experian Award for Building Stronger Communities \u8212\'20\'14 focused on food poverty. The company launched Community Food Connection, which uses an app to connect stores that have surplus food with local charities.\par \par \uc2 Creating a culture of sustainability can be difficult when employees are also juggling demands ranging from pressure to cut costs to meeting sales targets.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIt\u8217\'20\'19s making the linkage to the strategy and thinking about how that relates to the nature of the business,\u8221\'20\'1D says Prof Grayson. \u8220\'20\'1CThen it is the hard slog of aligning that with compensation, executive development, training and communications messages.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 For some, sustainability may mean saying no to business. \u8220\'20\'1CWe recently turned down working with a Middle Eastern bank and with a large tobacco company,\u8221\'20\'1D says Mr Wilkins of We Are Vista. He adds that external factors create hurdles to pursuing a sustainable strategy. \u8220\'20\'1CThe current level of disruption and the pace of change could give lots of people an excuse for not doing it.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 For some companies, however, a responsible business strategy helps to navigate disruption. This has been the case for Unipart, a winner of the Fujitsu Award for Responsible Business in the Digital Age. Rather than using digital technology to replace workers, the UK manufacturer is training employees to create new digital products and services, increasing their value to the company and enhancing their employability.\par \par \uc2 For Mr Wilkins, establishing a culture of sustainability helps build a collaborative spirit, equipping companies to respond quickly to shifts in the business landscape. \u8220\'20\'1CYou end up with a group of people connected to a bigger idea,\u8221\'20\'1D he says. \u8220\'20\'1CSo you get more cross-working and a willingness to change.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 The 2017 Responsible Business Awards winners\par \par \uc2 Business in the Community\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s Responsible Business of the Year\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF \uc2 Anglian Water Services\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF We Are Vista*\par \par \uc2 The Aviva Award for Championing an Ageing Workforce\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF \uc2 Barclays\par \par \uc2 The Barclays Award for Building Resilient Business\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF \uc2 Adler & Allan\par \par \uc2 The BITC Award for Environmental Leadership, supported by the \uc2 Department for \b \highlight22\uc2 Environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Food & Rural Affairs\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF \uc2 National Grid\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF The Lakes Free Range Egg Company*\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF Highly commended: British Sugar\par \par \uc2 The Experian Award for Building Stronger Communities\par \par \uc2 \u9679\'25\'CF \uc2 Tesco\pa