ft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2017 The Financial Times Ltd. All rights reserved. Please do not cut and paste FT articles and redistribute by email or post to the web. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Working in a diverse team is rarely as comfortable as being with people who look and think like you do.\par \par \uc2 But a growing body of research is beginning to demonstrate that companies run by such teams perform better. The lesson for managers? That any pain suffered along the way as you create a more inclusive workforce is more than outweighed by the gain.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Last year, a big study of more than 21,000 public companies in 91 countries by the Peterson Institute, a US think-tank, and EY, the professional services firm, found that bringing more women into higher management boosted profitability.\par \par \uc2 It said a company with 30 per cent female leadership could expect to add up to six percentage points to its net margin when compared with a similar business with no female leaders.\par \par \uc2 Later this year, McKinsey consultants will publish an update of 2015 research that makes a similar point in even greater detail. \u8220\'20\'1CIt\u8217\'20\'19s very clear that when women are at a critical mass, 20 per cent or more, at the decision-making level, it is that which is most correlated with higher performance. Parity in the workforce alone is not what matters most for value creation,\u8221\'20\'1D says \uc2 Vivian Hunt\uc2 , McKinsey\u8217\'20\'19s UK managing partner.\par \par \uc2 McKinsey used publicly available data from 2012-2015 to analyse gender diversity at the executive level at 754 companies across sectors and in all regions of the globe. The ethnic diversity of the top team was analysed at 495 companies across all regions.\par \par \uc2 It found that companies in the top quartile for gender diversity at executive level were 22 per cent more likely to outperform their national industry average than bottom-quartile companies in terms of profitability, as measured by earnings before interest and tax (ebit). For banks and insurers, return on equity was used as a proxy for financial performance.\par \par \uc2 When the research focused on a broader measure of performance, the distinction was even more marked.\par \par \uc2 Using \u8220\'20\'1Ceconomic profit\u8221\'20\'1D, which measures a company\u8217\'20\'19s ability to create value in excess of its weighted cost of capital, the differential between the top and the bottom quartile of companies was even greater, at 67 per cent.\par \par \uc2 The research also confirmed that there is a penalty for lack of diversity. Companies in the bottom quartile on both gender and ethnic diversity at the executive level underperformed companies in higher quartiles, whether this was measured in terms of operating profit performance or economic profit.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThere is a widening gap between those who are leading in this area and those who are not,\u8221\'20\'1D says Ms Hunt.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe leaders understand the rewards but also, increasingly \u8212\'20\'14 if you are not aware of how [diversity] links to your business strategy, or you are tone-deaf about your message on this \u8212\'20\'14 the penalties are much greater.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Having a diverse workforce as well as a diverse top team affected profitability too. The research found that greater gender diversity was linked to higher operating profitability at the whole-company level as well as in the executive team.\par \par \uc2 Measured by ebit performance, companies in the top quartile in terms of the gender diversity of their whole workforce were 46 per cent more likely than those in the bottom quartile to outperform their industry average.\par \par \uc2 McKinsey found that companies in the top-performing quartile for diversity shared several important policies or characteristics:\par \par \uc2 * The chief executive was committed publicly and internally to improving diversity.\par \par \uc2 * There were more women in executive positions.\par \par \uc2 * Diversity goals were part of the business strategy and value chain.\par \par \uc2 * The definition of diversity used was both tailored to the business strategy and to the local contexts in which the company operated.\par \par \uc2 Ms Hunt adds: \u8220\'20\'1CIn the top performers, diversity is genuinely integrated into a company\u8217\'20\'19s growth strategy. [It is] not an add-on for \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Their understanding of diversity reflects thoughtfulness and deliberate choices about what characteristics matter most for their companies.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Below are examples of how some multinationals have applied successful strategies:\par \par \uc2 Achieve a more diverse workforce: strategies that work\par \par \uc2 1. Commitment from the chief executive\par \par \uc2 Westpac\par \par \uc2 Banking, Australia\par \par \uc2 * CEO \uc2 Brian Hartzer\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s performance targets include non-financial diversity metrics\par \par \uc2 * Former CEO \uc2 Gail Kelly\uc2  set a target in 2010 of 40% female representation in leadership roles; new target is 50% by 2017\par \par \uc2 * Head of inclusion and diversity reports directly to CEO\par \par \uc2 Shiseido\par \par \uc2 Cosmetics, Japan\par \par \uc2 * CEO \uc2 Masahiko Uotani\uc2  has made public statements about the importance of a diverse and inclusive workforce\par \par \uc2 * He has a goal of 50/50 women and men on \uc2 Shiseido\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s board by 2010\par \par \uc2 Salesforce\par \par \uc2 Cloud software, US\par \par \uc2 * \uc2 Marc Benioff\uc2 , Salesforce CEO, has stated that \uc2 Salesforce\uc2  is \u8220\'20\'1Cworking for equality, fighting inequality\u8221\'20\'1D, and is a vocal advocate of pay equity\par \par \uc2 2. Design targeted transformatory initiatives\par \par \uc2 Unilever\par \par \uc2 Consumer goods, UK/Netherlands\par \par \uc2 * Gender-balanced succession plans required for senior leadership roles\par \par \uc2 * Diversity training mandatory for leadership roles\par \par \uc2 * Global mentoring programme launched for high-potential female managers\par \par \uc2 Wipro\par \par \uc2 IT services, India\par \par \uc2 * Women of \uc2 Wipro\uc2  is a set of initiatives based on a tailored approach to women at different stages in their career\par \par \uc2 * The company uses specialised online tools such as Globe Smart to develop sensitivity towards different cultures across the business\par \par \uc2 3. Define diversity priorities based on your growth strategy\par \par \uc2 Johnson & Johnson\par \par \uc2 Healthcare, US\par \par \uc2 * Diversity and inclusion efforts focus on three areas aligned to a strategic plan\par \par \uc2 UPS Package\par \par \uc2 Delivery/logistics, US\par \par \uc2 * Efforts on diversity and inclusion have made its business more sustainable by helping it \u8220\'20\'1Cbetter understand and meet customer needs, as well as strengthening our workplace \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 4. Use a diversity strategy to maximise local impact\par \par \uc2 Salesforce\par \par \uc2 * CEO has advocated for LGBTI rights, boycotting US states with discriminatory bills targeting the LGBTI community\par \par \uc2 Sodexo\par \par \uc2 Food services, France\par \par \uc2 * Diversity and inclusion initiatives vary based on country and focus group: for example, training members of a local community in Peru, or a mentoring programme for 50+ years old in France\par \par \uc2 Source: \uc2 McKinsey & Co\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 cwkdiv : \uc2 Workplace Diversity | cfmex : \uc2 Women Executives | c41 : \uc2 Management | c42 : \uc2 Labor/Personnel | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpin : \uc2 C&E Industry News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx72