0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2018. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Good Monday. Here\u8217\'20\'19s what we\u8217\'20\'19re watching:\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The tech reckoning is gaining momentum.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Ripple\u8217\'20\'19s XRP virtual currency plunged over the past day.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 GoPro\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s shares dropped after the company announced disappointing sales forecasts.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Could a sale of \uc2 Twitter\uc2  happen this year?\par \par \uc2 Want this in your own email inbox ? {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://p.nytimes.com/email/re?location=pMJKdIFVI6pghfX2HXfSzxRpdoyDWYNW92ocucjMeAZSlSDUpGC59mB7DzVdTE2LNCS5MGulkt4OtYdxG7o6mFvAdcmG9SO57PjEtjY1oUuXS6MzkGhmVA==&campaign_id=97&instance_id=105993&segment_id=115746&user_id=b6f684c312bdf03b09c4c5a79e680ec1&regi_id=5411894"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Here\u8217\'20\'19s the sign-up}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The tech reckoning is gaining momentum.\par \par \uc2 American technology giants are facing an increasing backlash. \uc2 Google\uc2 -parent Alphabet, \uc2 Facebook\uc2  and \uc2 Twitter\uc2  have drawn scrutiny from lawmakers over the manipulation of social media during the 2016 election by Russian operatives. Critics of \uc2 Amazon\uc2  say it is killing jobs. Across the pond, European regulators have gone after American tech firms over privacy and what officials deem anticompetitive behavior.\par \par \uc2 Now \uc2 Jana Partners\uc2  and pension giant \uc2 Calstrs{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/08/business/apple-investors-children.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 are pushing Apple}}}\uc2  to do more to protect its youngest users from the effects of digital technology.\par \par \uc2 Writes Shira Ovide of Bloomberg Gadfly:\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1COne letter from \uc2 Calstrs\uc2  and Jana may amount to nothing. It\u8217\'20\'19s becoming increasingly clear, however, that scrutiny over technology companies and their products isn\u8217\'20\'19t going away.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThere will be much discussion about whether technology companies, or people and parents, bear responsibility for limiting the harmful effects of technology. Even smartphone overuse isn\u8217\'20\'19t Apple\u8217\'20\'19s problem alone. Its gadgets are gateways to people hooked on \uc2 Instagram\uc2 , \uc2 YouTube\uc2 , Snapchat and much more. We are all the problem, and the technology companies are all the problem.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Still, compared to \uc2 Facebook\uc2 , \uc2 Google\uc2  or Snap, Apple is an unusual choice for the investors to target, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/08/business/dealbook/tech-backlash-catches-up-to-apple.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 writes Jennifer Saba of Breakingviews}}}\uc2 . The company makes hardware and uses privacy as a selling point. For those reasons, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.breakingviews.com/considered-view/apple-provides-hedge-against-global-tech-backlash/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Apple was expected to avoid the worst of the blowback}}}\uc2 . But its targeting shows the extent to which the backlash against tech is gaining momentum: Writes Ms. Saba:\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CSilicon Valley used to enjoy an exalted status, but questions about the role of social media in the 2016 presidential election and the way digital technologies may threaten jobs and promote monopolies are breeding skepticism. The new focus on Apple shows how much technology has lost its halo.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Rick Perry\u8217\'20\'19s Plan to Rescue Struggling Coal and Nuclear Plants Is Rejected\par \par \uc2 Federal regulators have {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://elibrary.ferc.gov/idmws/file_list.asp?document_id=14633130"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 rejected}}}\uc2  a proposal by Energy Secretary Rick Perry to subsidize struggling coal and nuclear plants, in a major blow to the Trump administration\u8217\'20\'19s efforts to revive America\u8217\'20\'19s declining coal industry, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/08/climate/trump-coal-nuclear.html?hp&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&clickSource=story-heading&module=first-column-region&region=top-news&WT.nav=top-news"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the NYT reports}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In September, Mr. Perry {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://energy.gov/articles/secretary-perry-urges-ferc-take-swift-action-address-threats-grid-resiliency"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 warned}}}\uc2  that the loss of these plants could threaten the \u8220\'20\'1Creliability and resiliency of our nation\u8217\'20\'19s grid\u8221\'20\'1D and asked the \uc2 Federal Energy Regulatory Commission\uc2 , which oversees regional electricity markets, to guarantee financial returns for power plants that can stockpile at least 90 days\u8217\'20\'19 worth of fuel on-site \u8212\'20\'14 which, in effect, meant propping up uncompetitive coal and nuclear units. (Natural gas plants are typically fed by pipeline and would not qualify.)\par \par \uc2 While a few utilities with significant coal and nuclear capacity supported the idea, Mr. Perry\u8217\'20\'19s proposal {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.utilitydive.com/news/doe-nopr-opponents-no-basis-for-expanded-fpa-to-justify-coal-nuke-cost-re/508123/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 generated a fierce backlash}}}\uc2  from a broad coalition of energy companies, free-market groups and former regulators.\par \par \uc2 Ripple takes a big hit.\par \par \uc2 Only last week, Ripple appeared to lay claim to the biggest alternative to Bitcoin. That isn\u8217\'20\'19t the case anymore.\par \par \uc2 The price of Ripple\u8217\'20\'19s XRP virtual currency {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://coinmarketcap.com/currencies/ripple/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 has plunged about 27 percent}}}\uc2  over the past 24 hours, reaching $2.47 this morning, according to CoinMarketCap. Ripple\u8217\'20\'19s total market capitalization has fallen back below that of \uc2 Ethereum\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 To be fair, other virtual currencies \u8212\'20\'14 including Bitcoin \u8212\'20\'14 are falling as well.\par \par \uc2 It was only last week: Investors breathlessly touted Ripple co-founder Chris Larsen, who owns a significant amount of XRP, as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/04/technology/bitcoin-ripple.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 richer than Mark Zuckerberg}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The breathlessness hasn\u8217\'20\'19t abated: Shares in \uc2 Seagate\uc2  were {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://uk.businessinsider.com/ripple-xrp-owned-by-seagate-report-surges-after-report-it-may-own-billions-ripple-2018-1?r=US&IR=T"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 briefly up more than 10 percent}}}\uc2  on Monday amid excited speculation that the hard drive company owned a huge stake in XRP as part of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.coindesk.com/seagate-ripple-investment-shows-were-serious-about-blockchain-tech/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 its investment in Ripple}}}\uc2  almost three years ago. (It\u8217\'20\'19s not clear that\u8217\'20\'19s actually the case.)\par \par \uc2 \u8212\'20\'14 Michael J. de la Merced\par \par \uc2 GoPro\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s woes continue to grow.\par \par \uc2 Its announcement of preliminary fourth-quarter results today compounds the troubles for what has been one of the most disappointing market debutantes in recent years.\par \par \uc2 The company issued a revenue forecast that was lighter than analysts were expecting. And the action-camera maker announced its latest efforts to turn around its business:\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Laying off at least 254 employees, bringing its headcount to under 1,000 worldwide\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Its founder and C.E.O., \uc2 Nick Woodman\uc2 , reducing his cash compensation this year to $1.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Getting out of the drone market amid \u8220\'20\'1Ca hostile regulatory \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8221\'20\'1D in Europe and the U.S.\par \par \uc2 Over all, \uc2 GoPro\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s shares have fallen 79 percent since {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/06/26/gopro-shares-jump-on-market-debut/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the company\u8217\'20\'19s I.P.O.}}}\uc2  three-and-a-half years ago.\par \par \uc2 \u8212\'20\'14 Michael J. de la Merced\par \par \uc2 How much of its tax windfall will Apple spend on buybacks?\par \par \uc2 Steven Milunovich\uc2 , an analyst at UBS, expects the iPhone maker to use the overseas cash it repatriates to buy back $122 billion in stock through 2019.\par \par \uc2 The company {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/04/business/corporate-tax-cuts.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 holds about $252 billion}}}\uc2  cash offshore. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnbc.com/2018/01/08/buy-apple-because-it-could-buy-back-more-than-120-billion-of-stock.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Mr. Milunovich via CNBC writes}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CRepatriation of ~$250bn of offshore cash should increase the rate of Apple\u8217\'20\'19s share buybacks since the company believes the stock remains attractive in that its services business is undervalued.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Apple has bought back more than $165 billion of stock over the past five years.\par \par \uc2 Is 2018 the year that \uc2 Twitter\uc2  is sold?\par \par \uc2 The analyst \uc2 Rich Greenfield\uc2  of BTIG thinks so. Leading his list of predictions for the year is speculation that the social network would finally {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.btigresearch.com/2018/01/08/btigs-top-18-media-predictions-and-events-to-watch-for-in-2018-top18for18/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 become the target of deal-making}}}\uc2 . (Remember that {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/15/business/dealbook/salesforce-twitter.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Salesforce had held talks}}}\uc2  to buy the company in the fall of 2016.)\par \par \uc2 From Mr. Greenfield\u8217\'20\'19s note:\par \par \uc2 Twitter\uc2  offers a unique acquisition opportunity for any company looking to own breaking news, politics and sports, infused with video on mobile devices with tens of millions of daily active users across the world. Add to that a vast treasure trove of data on its users and a \uc2 Twitter\uc2  acquisition becomes compelling for many companies across the TMT universe.\par \par \uc2 Who would buy \uc2 Twitter\uc2 ? Maybe \uc2 Salesforce\uc2  comes back. Or maybe \uc2 Google\uc2  does. Or \uc2 Microsoft\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Other predictions\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 AT&T\uc2  will defeat the Justice Department in the court battle over \uc2 Time Warner\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 CBS\uc2  and \uc2 Viacom\uc2  finally combine.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Spotify will go public this year, but may sell itself down the road.\par \par \uc2 \u8212\'20\'14 Michael J. de la Merced\par \par \uc2 How long can \uc2 Nvidia\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s rally last?\par \par \uc2 The chip-maker\u8217\'20\'19s stock is up 2.5 percent Monday. The driver? News that \uc2 Nvidia\uc2  will partner with Uber and \uc2 Volkswagen\uc2  on autonomous driving projects.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2018/01/08/technology/08reuters-tech-ces-nvidia.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Reuters reports}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \u8220\'20\'1CNvidia CEO Jensen Huang said at the CES technology conference in Las Vegas that Uber\u8217\'20\'19s self-driving car fleet was using their technology to help its autonomous cars perceive the world and make split-second decisions.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \u8220\'20\'1CWith \uc2 Volkswagen\uc2 , \uc2 Nvidia\uc2  said it was infusing its artificial intelligence technology into the German automakers\u8217\'20\'19 future lineup, using their new Drive IX platform. The technology will enable so-called \u8220\'20\'1Cintelligent co-pilot\u8221\'20\'1D capabilities based on processing sensor data inside and outside the car.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Some context: Shares of \uc2 Nvidia\uc2  more than doubled over the past 12 months after a roughly 200 percent gain in 2016. The rally in \uc2 Nvidia\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s shares {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://blogs.wsj.com/moneybeat/2017/06/08/can-nvidias-shares-double-to-300/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 has come as demand for chips}}}\uc2  to power data centers, artificial intelligence, autonomous driving and gaming has surged.\par \par \uc2 Nvidia\uc2  said that \u8220\'20\'1C320 companies involved in self-driving cars - whether software developers, automakers and their suppliers, sensor and mapping companies - are using Nvidia Drive, formerly branded as the Drive PX2,\u8221\'20\'1D Reuters reports.\par \par \uc2 Deutsche Bank\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s woes continue.\par \par \uc2 The German bank is down seven percent the past two days after it said it{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.reuters.com/article/us-deutsche-bank-tax/deutsche-bank-to-post-third-consecutive-annual-loss-idUSKBN1EU1JB"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  would post a small loss }}}\uc2 for 2017, its third consecutive annual. Weak trading and a $1.8 billion hit from the United State\u8217\'20\'19s tax overhaul are the main culprits.\par \par \uc2 Of those, \uc2 Deutsche Bank\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s trading woes should be more concerning to shareholders, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.breakingviews.com/considered-view/deutsche-bank-is-portent-of-investment-bank-gloom/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 writes Christopher Thompson of Breakingviews}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The bank said sales and trading revenue was expected to decline 22 percent in the fourth quarter from a year ago. While \uc2 Deutsche Bank\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s trading performance has not be appreciably worse than its European rivals, the decline in its shares \u8220\'20\'1Cis that it is more dependent on this revenue than other big investment banks.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CEquities and fixed income sales and trading brought in more than 31 percent of Deutsche\u8217\'20\'19s total revenue in the third quarter of 2017, compared with around 28 percent at \uc2 Credit Suisse\uc2  and 19 percent at \uc2 Barclays\uc2 . The German group also lacks a consistent source of stable earnings similar to \uc2 Credit Suisse\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s wealth management franchise or \uc2 Barclays\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s UK retail bank.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 That means that \u8220\'20\'1Cwithout a pickup in volatility or client activity, trading revenues \u8211\'20\'13 and shareholders \u8211\'20\'13 remain stuck in a rut,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr. Thompson writes.\par \par \uc2 If your business flight to New York was disrupted this weekend, here\u8217\'20\'19s why.\par \par \uc2 Jason Rabinowitz of The Points Guy explained how John F. Kennedy International Airport in particular functions \u8212\'20\'14 and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://thepointsguy.com/2018/01/why-did-jfk-struggle-flight-backlog/?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 why its operations were severely disrupted}}}\uc2  even after the \u8220\'20\'1Cbomb cyclone\u8221\'20\'1D of last week.\par \par \uc2 Among the interesting pieces of trivia to emerge from the piece:\par \par \uc2 Essentially, each terminal at JFK is its own little fiefdom with separate operations, management and employees. If an airline calls Terminal 7 home, that\u8217\'20\'19s the only terminal it\u8217\'20\'19s allowed to use. Even if Terminal 4 has a dozen empty gates, an airline slated for Terminal 7 may have to wait hours for a gate to open at Terminal 7.\par \par \uc2 Here\u8217\'20\'19s Mr. Rabinowitz\u8217\'20\'19s concluding thought:\par \par \uc2 Savvy travelers all know to avoid NYC area airports whenever possible, and this winter storm drove that point home once again.\par \par \uc2 \u8212\'20\'14 Michael J. de la Merced\par \par \uc2 Intel\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s C.E.O. is in the hot seat, just in time for CES.\par \par \uc2 Questions \uc2 Brian Krzanich{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/07/technology/intel-chip-security.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 is likely to face}}}\uc2  about as he prepares for a keynote speech at the biggest convention in consumer electronics:\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 How well will planned fixes work against Meltdown and Spectre, the two computer chip security flaws that affect most of the world\u8217\'20\'19s processors?\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Can \uc2 Intel\uc2  design new chips without either of the problems?\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Were the $39 million worth of stock sales he made in November, after the flaws were discovered but before they were disclosed, really just part of a prearranged trading plan?\par \par \uc2 What he would prefer to talk about: Augmented reality and self-driving cars.\par \par \uc2 Today\u8217\'20\'19s talking point, from Nathaniel Fick, the C.E.O. of the cybersecurity company Endgame, in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/08/opinion/cybersecurity-breach-spectre-meltdown.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 an NYT Op-Ed}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 From a corporate governance and accountability perspective, cybersecurity today is being treated like accounting was before the fallout from the \uc2 Enron\uc2  scandal inspired the Sarbanes-Oxley Act\u8217\'20\'19s increased standards for corporate disclosures.\par \par \uc2 The tech flyaround, CES edition\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The convention\u8217\'20\'19s organizers said they were seeking more women speakers. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.cnet.com/news/ces-2018-women-keynotes-speakers/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 CNET}}}\uc2 )\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Google\uc2  is preparing to step up its fight against \uc2 Amazon\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s Echo. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.ft.com/content/582249ae-f199-11e7-b220-857e26d1aca4"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 FT}}}\uc2 )\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Amazon\uc2  isn\u8217\'20\'19t sitting still and wants to put its Alexa virtual assistant in more and more devices. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.recode.net/2018/1/6/16855310/amazon-alexa-bose-headphones-wearables"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Recode}}}\uc2 )\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Superfast 5G wireless internet will be a big focal point of the convention. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://uk.businessinsider.com/the-trends-and-events-that-will-matter-at-ces-2018-2018-1?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Business Insider}}}\uc2 )\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The proliferation of next-generation streaming services is a reminder of how far online video has come since the debut of Web TV 20 years ago, Neal Mohan, YouTube\u8217\'20\'19s chief product officer writes. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://variety.com/2018/digital/opinion/ces-a-reminder-of-how-far-tv-tech-has-come-guest-column-1202644545/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Variety}}}\uc2 )\par \par \uc2 #MeToo and Oprah take center stage at the Golden Globes.\par \par \uc2 Among the highlights from last night\u8217\'20\'19s awards, where {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/07/movies/golden-globes.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the uniform was black}}}\uc2  to acknowledge systemic harassment and sexism in Hollywood:\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Oprah Winfrey\uc2 , who received the Cecil B. DeMille Award for lifetime achievement, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/07/movies/oprah-winfrey-golden-globes-speech-transcript.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 used her acceptance speech}}}\uc2  as a call to arms, saying, \u8220\'20\'1CA new day is on the horizon.\u8221\'20\'1D Speculation has arisen about {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mog-golden-globes-oprah-president-20180107-story.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 whether she }}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mog-golden-globes-oprah-president-20180107-story.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 might}}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mog-golden-globes-oprah-president-20180107-story.html?dlbk"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  run for president}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The actresses Debra Messing and Eva Longoria used red-carpet interviews to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/07/movies/debra-messing-catt-sadler-e-news.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 chasti