n0\lin0 \uc2 In recent quarters, net income has been boosted by taxpayer funds Intesa received as part of a deal to take control of the good assets of two failed Venetian banks and help shore up confidence in the fragile banking system last summer.\par \par \uc2 On Tuesday, \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo\uc2  said it would cut its net non-performing loans to \u8364\'20\'AC12.1bn from \u8364\'20\'AC22.5bn by 2021, with its cost of risk falling to 41 basis points from 81 basis points in 2017. Net income ratio would rise 12 per cent to \u8364\'20\'AC6bn over the period of the plan from \u8364\'20\'AC3.8bn in 2017, and its payout ratio would fall from 85 per cent for 2018 to 70 per cent for 2021.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThis is setting a new story of growth for \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D chief executive \uc2 Carlo Messina\uc2  told investors on a conference call. \u8220\'20\'1CWe can play the game of being one of the top banks in Europe\u8221\'20\'1D.\par \par \uc2 Mr Messina said the bank intended to pump more than \u8364\'20\'AC300bn into the Italian real economy by 2021, including mid and long term lending to Italian businesses.\par \par \uc2 Pro-forma fully loaded common equity Tier 1 ratio would be 13.1 per cent in 2012 including regulatory impacts. \u8220\'20\'1CThere is no risk to the bank from the new regulatory \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr Messina said.\par \par \uc2 Operating costs would fall 0.9 per cent to \u8364\'20\'AC9.5bn over the course of the plan. Operating margin would increase to 9.1 per cent to \u8364\'20\'AC11.4bn in 2017.\par \par \uc2 Mr Messina also said \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo\uc2 , Italy\u8217\'20\'19s largest domestic bank which is already a big donor to the arts in Italy, intended to be a \u8220\'20\'1Cworld class reference model\u8221\'20\'1D in \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This would include an initiative to provide \u8220\'20\'1Cfood and shelter for people in need\u8221\'20\'1D by allocating funds to pay for 10,000 meals a day, 6,000 dormitory beds a month and 3,000 items of medicine and clothes.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 nvoamb : \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo S.p.A.\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i81402 : \uc2 Commercial Banking | i814 : \uc2 Banking | ibnk : \uc2 Banking/Credit | ifinal : \uc2 Financial Services\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c151 : \uc2 Earnings | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | c15 : \uc2 Financial Performance | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpin : \uc2 C&E Industry News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctl