n0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 2018 The Financial Times Ltd. All rights reserved. Please do not cut and paste FT articles and redistribute by email or post to the web. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo\uc2  on Tuesday unveiled an ambitious four-year plan to almost halve its stock of bad loans and boost net income.\par \par \uc2 The long-awaited strategy reboot aims to rebuild investor confidence after a turbulent period for Italy\u8217\'20\'19s banking industry in which Intesa has remained profitable but has seen momentum slow.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Shares in Intesa, one of Italy\u8217\'20\'19s most healthiest banks, rose 1.8 per cent despite volatility on global markets, as \uc2 Carlo Messina\uc2 , the chief executive, revealed the new business plan.\par \par \uc2 In recent quarters, net income has been boosted by taxpayer funds Intesa received as part of a deal to take control of the good assets of two failed Venetian banks and help shore up confidence in the fragile banking system last summer.\par \par \uc2 On Tuesday, Intesa said it would cut its net non-performing loans to \u8364\'20\'AC12.1bn from \u8364\'20\'AC22.5bn by 2021, with its cost of risk falling to 41 basis points from 81bp in 2017. Net income ratio would rise 12 per cent to \u8364\'20\'AC6bn over the period of the plan from \u8364\'20\'AC3.8bn in 2017, and its payout ratio would fall from 85 per cent for 2018 to 70 per cent for 2021.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThis is setting a new story of growth for \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr Messina told investors on a conference call. \u8220\'20\'1CWe can play the game of being one of the top banks in Europe\u8221\'20\'1D.\par \par \uc2 Mr Messina said the bank intended to pump more than \u8364\'20\'AC300bn into the Italian real economy by 2021, including mid- and long-term lending to Italian businesses.\par \par \uc2 Pro-forma fully loaded common equity tier 1 ratio would be 13.1 per cent in 2021, including regulatory impacts. \u8220\'20\'1CThere is no risk to the bank from the new regulatory \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr Messina said.\par \par \uc2 Operating costs would fall 0.9 per cent to \u8364\'20\'AC9.5bn over the course of the plan. Operating margin would increase to 9.1 per cent to \u8364\'20\'AC11.4bn in 2021.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIntesa has the best mix of revenues in Europe and one of the strongest capital in the industry. This creates a unique investment opportunity as there is a mix of quality of cash flow and dividends,\u8221\'20\'1D said \uc2 Davide Serra\uc2 , CEO and founder of Algebris, who owns equity and AT 1 securities in the bank.\par \par \uc2 Intesa\u8217\'20\'19s move to slash its holding of bad loans, in part by using some of its capital, comes after more than a year of pressure on the share prices of Italian bank stocks over their holdings of soured debt.\par \par \uc2 Eurozone bank supervisors signalled last autumn they intended to take an increasingly tough line on almost \u8364\'20\'AC1tn of NPLs left after the region\u8217\'20\'19s financial crisis. In a so-called addendum, the \uc2 European Central Bank\uc2  unveiled plans to require banks to hold more collateral against new lending that turned sour, and potentially for a backlog of bad loans.\par \par \uc2 Mr Messina acknowledged that Intesa\u8217\'20\'19s \u8220\'20\'1Cacceleration\u8221\'20\'1D in a plan to offload its bad loans could have an impact on other Italian lenders, pushing them to slash their bad loans at a faster rate than anticipated.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1COur NPL plan is unquestionably a point of reference for Italy,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 He also hit out at eurozone bank regulators for putting Italian banks under focus over their bad loans over the past two years, while predicting French and German banks would come under pressure for their holding of Level 2 and Level 3 assets in the coming months. Mr Messina\u8217\'20\'19s comments echo a \uc2 Bank of Italy\uc2  report published in December arguing the eurozone should be more careful about the opaque instruments.\par \par \uc2 Mr Messina also said the bank, a big donor to the arts in Italy, intended to be a \u8220\'20\'1Cworld class reference model\u8221\'20\'1D in \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 . This would include an initiative to provide \u8220\'20\'1Cfood and shelter for people in need\u8221\'20\'1D by allocating funds to pay for 10,000 meals a day, 6,000 dormitory beds a month and 3,000 items of medicine and clothes.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 nvoamb : \uc2 Intesa Sanpaolo S.p.A.\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i81402 : \uc2 Commercial Banking | i814 : \uc2 Banking | ibnk : \uc2 Banking/Credit | ifinal : \uc2 Financial Services\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c151 : \uc2 Earnings | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | c15 : \uc2 Financial Performance | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpin : \uc2 C&E Industry News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clp